    ‚ąá {r}‚ÜźFill_META list;this;isRef;scriptRef
    ‚ćĚ Runs a loop on all items in `list` wich can be a single ref or the fully qualified name
    ‚ćĚ of a function or a vector (and mixture) of both. Refs are pointing to classes, interfaces
    ‚ćĚ or namespaces while fully qualified names are special cases were a single function in an
    ‚ćĚ ordinary namespace is expected to carry comments that represent the documentation.
    ‚ćĚ
    ‚ćĚ This function (and its sub-functions) assemble a variable _META with contains for every
    ‚ćĚ single "thing" (method, field, function, operator, variable, depending on the source to be
    ‚ćĚ investigated) all information ADOC is supposed to show in one way or another. Later from
    ‚ćĚ this a list (`Info`) or HTML output (`Browse`) is generated
      r‚Üź‚ć¨
      isRef‚Üź{‚ćĶ‚ČĘ‚ćē‚ćĶ}
      :If 2>‚Č°list
      :AndIf ~isRef list
          list‚Üź,‚äālist
      :EndIf
      :For this :In list
          :If isRef this
              scriptRef‚Üźthis
              :If _embeddedClassesFlag
              :AndIf 0=‚ČĘ_embeddedClassNames
                  _embeddedClassNames‚ÜźReportEmbeddedClasses scriptRef
              :EndIf
              :If 0=‚ČĘ_embeddedClassNames
                  Analyze scriptRef
              :Else
                  _embeddedClassNames Analyze scriptRef
              :EndIf
          :Else
              ‚éē‚Üź'Huuh?! What''s that: ',this
          :EndIf
      :EndFor
    ‚ąá

