      :EndIf
    ‚ąá

    ‚ąá {filename}‚Üź{x}Browse scriptRef;PathToExe;browserPath;bool;allowed;Note;‚éēTRAP
         ‚ćĚ This is the main method when ADOC is used without creating an instance and the documentation
         ‚ćĚ is supposed to be beautified and displayed in a browser.\\
         ‚ćĚ By default, the default browser is used to display the result. The exception is that when
         ‚ćĚ the current session is connected to Ride, then the Ride browser is used.\\
         ‚ćĚ You can change this by setting `BrowserPath` to the full path pointing
         ‚ćĚ to an executable. However, this has no effect when the session is connected to Ride.\\
         ‚ćĚ You can set the following parameters via a parameter space; see `CreateBrowseDefaults` for
         ‚ćĚ how to create a parameter space with default values.\\
         ‚ćĚ Such a parameter space can then be passed as left argument to `Browse`:\\
         ‚ćĚ * BrowserPath
         ‚ćĚ * Title
         ‚ćĚ * IgnorePattern
         ‚ćĚ * Inherit
         ‚ćĚ * embeddedClassesFlag
         ‚ćĚ * ignoreCopyright
         ‚ćĚ * ignoreHistory
         ‚ćĚ * ignoreVersion\\
         ‚ćĚ Note that specifying a parameter via a parameter space does
         ‚ćĚ **not** save the value permanently.\\
         ‚ćĚ The right argument can be a single ref pointing to a class, an interface or a
         ‚ćĚ namespace. It can also be a vector of such references.\\
         ‚ćĚ See [Reference to a script](#) for details.\\
         ‚ćĚ Prior to version 6.0 of ADOC it could also be the name of a function; this is
         ‚ćĚ not supported any more.\\
         ‚ćĚ ## Reference to a script
         ‚ćĚ If `scriptRef` is empty, the previously created HTML is displayed.\\
         ‚ćĚ Note that in this case the HTML remains untouched. Therefore it can still be used for other purposes.\\
         ‚ćĚ You can pass the name of one or more embedded classes --- classes locally defined
         ‚ćĚ within a class script; see `ADOC` itself as an example --- or embedded namespaces.
         ‚ćĚ You get then a document which contains only these embedded
         ‚ćĚ class(es)/namespace(s).\\
         ‚ćĚ Note that this syntax is available only when a single
         ‚ćĚ script is specified in the right argument.
      :Access Public shared
      ‚éēTRAP‚Üź(999 'E' '‚ąÜEM ‚éēsignal 11')((0 1000)'N')
      filename‚Üź''
      _Title‚Üź''
      Init_HTML
      :If 0<‚éēNC'x'
          :If 9=‚éēNC'x' ‚ćĚ is it a parameter space?
              allowed‚ÜźCreateBrowseDefaults.‚ąÜList[;1]
              :If 0‚ąäbool‚Üź(x.‚éēNL-2)‚ąäallowed
                  11 ‚éēSIGNAL‚ć®‚ąÜEM‚Üź'Invalid: ',‚äÉ{‚ćļ,',',‚ćĶ}/(~bool)‚ĆŅx.‚éēNL-2
              :EndIf
              bool‚Üź(x.‚éēNL-2)‚ąäallowed~‚äā'RefToUnicodeFile'
              x.‚éēEX(~bool)‚ĆŅx.‚éēNL 2      ‚ćĚ "RefToUnicodeFile" is deprecated
          :AndIf 0‚Č†‚ČĘx.‚éēNL 2 9
              ‚éēSHADOW¬®'_',¬®x.‚éēNL-2     ‚ćĚ Keep them local - we don't want to overwrite the real fields/props
              ‚ćé¬®GetVarsFrom x
          :Else
              (‚ąÜEM‚Üź'This syntax is retired; set "embeddedClassesFlag" in a parameter space instead')‚éēSIGNAL 11
          :EndIf
      :EndIf
     
      :If 0=‚ČĘscriptRef
          :If _htmlFinalised
              tempFilename‚ÜźGetTempFileName
          :Else
              11 ‚éēSIGNAL‚ć®‚ąÜEM‚Üź'I''m afraid, there is no HTML ready for being displayed'
          :EndIf
      :Else
          'Right argument must be a reference pointing to a class, namespace or interface'‚éēSIGNAL 11/‚ć®~‚ąß/(|‚éēNC¬®‚äā‚ąė‚ćē¬®scriptRef)‚ąä9.1 9.4 9.5
     
          Fill_META scriptRef     ‚ćĚ ‚Üź‚Üź‚Üź The work horse!
     
          :If 0‚Č†‚ČĘ_META
              _WithRunningNumbers‚Üź{¬Į1=‚ćĶ:1<‚ČĘ_META ‚čĄ ‚ćĶ}_WithRunningNumbers
              CreateHtml ‚ć¨
              :If 0=‚ČĘ_HTML
                  ‚éē‚Üź'Nothing found'
              :Else
                  FinaliseHtml ‚ć¨
                  _Filename‚Üź(¬Į4‚ÜďP.FilesAndDirs.GetTempFilename2''),'.html'
                  SaveHtml2File _Filename
              :EndIf
              filename‚Üź_Filename
          :EndIf
      :EndIf
      :If 0‚Č†‚ČĘfilename
      :AndIf view
          View filename
      :EndIf
      _embeddedClassName‚Üź''
