    ‚ąá r‚ÜźMakeAnchor(html pattern);where;i;ref
     ‚ćĚ Look for "pattern" in html and make all occurencies an anchor.
     ‚ćĚ Typically "pattern" is something like "http://x.y.z" or "mailto:x@y.z"
     ‚ćĚ of "file:///foo.txt"; You can prevent this from happening with a leading "!"
      :If 0‚Č†‚ČĘwhere‚Üź‚ĆĹ{‚ćĶ/‚ć≥‚ČĘ‚ćĶ}pattern‚ć∑r‚Üźhtml
          :For i :In where
              :If '!'=¬Į1‚ÜĎr‚Üź(i-1)‚ĆĹr
                  r‚Üź(-i-2)‚ĆĹ¬Į1‚Üďr
              :Else
                  ref‚Üź{‚ćĶ‚ÜĎ‚ć®¬Į1+‚Ćä/‚ćĶ‚ć≥'  <'}r
                  r‚Üź(-i-1)‚ĆĹ(('a class="externallink" href="',(ref),'"')tag ref),(‚ČĘref)‚Üďr
              :EndIf
          :EndFor
      :EndIf
    ‚ąá

    ‚ąá (prop remark)‚ÜźSplitAtLamp data;bool;firstLine
       ‚ćĚ Split "data" not only at the lamp (easy) but takes text into account, too.
       ‚ćĚ So this   :'foo‚Üź''‚ćĚ''  ‚ćĚ assign lamp<br>    is handled correctly, too.
      remark‚Üź''
      (firstLine data)‚Üź{(1‚äÉ‚ćĶ)(1‚Üď‚ćĶ)}data
      data‚Üź(':'‚Č†‚ÜĎ¬®data~¬®' ')/data ‚ćĚ remove lines like ":Access" and similars
      :If '‚ćĚ'‚ąäfirstLine/‚ć®bool‚Üź~MaskText firstLine
          (prop remark)‚ÜźfirstLine{((‚ćĶ-1)‚ÜĎ‚ćļ)({‚ćĶ‚Üď‚ć®+/‚ąß\' '=‚ćĶ}‚ćĶ‚Üď‚ćļ)}'‚ćĚ'‚ć≥‚ć®bool\bool/firstLine
          prop‚Üź{‚ćĶ‚Üď‚ć®+/‚ąß\' '=‚ćĶ}({‚ćĶ‚Üď‚ć®‚ćĶ‚ć≥' '}prop)
      :Else
          prop‚ÜźfirstLine
      :EndIf
      :If 0‚Č†‚ČĘdata‚Üź({‚ąß\'‚ćĚ'=‚ÜĎ‚ćĶ~' '}¬®data)/data
          remark‚Üź{‚ćĶ/‚ć®0<‚ÜĎ‚ąė‚ćī¬®,¬®‚ćĶ}(‚äāremark),data
      :EndIf
      remark‚Üź{0 1‚ąä‚ć®‚Č°‚ćĶ:‚äā‚ćĶ ‚čĄ ‚ćĶ}remark
      remark‚Üź{‚ćĶ‚Üď‚ć®+/‚ąß\‚ćĶ‚ąä' ‚ćĚ'}¬®remark
    ‚ąá

