    ‚ąá r‚Üź{convertHeader}PolishComments(markdown hasContainers isContainer chapterNo);ns;parms
    ‚ćĚ Interprets the "leading" comments as extended Markdown.
    ‚ćĚ Via the (optional) left argument one can force any headers in `markdown` to be converted to <h6>.
    ‚ćĚ This makes sense in case it is a function/operator.
      :If 0=‚ČĘ‚ąämarkdown
          r‚Üź''
      :Else
          convertHeader‚Üź{0<‚éēNC ‚ćĶ:‚ćé‚ćĶ ‚čĄ 0}'convertHeader'
          :If convertHeader
              markdown‚Üź'(^\s{0,3})#{1,5} '‚éēR'\1###### '‚ä£markdown  ‚ćĚ All headers are converted to level 6.
          :EndIf
          markdown‚ÜźReplaceDoubleBackslashByNewLine markdown
          markdown‚ÜźisContainer‚Üď,markdown
          :If 0‚Č†‚ČĘmarkdown‚Üź(‚Ćä/+/¬®‚ąß\¬®markdown=' ')‚Üď¬®markdown
              parms‚ÜźP.MarkAPL.CreateParms
              parms.verbose‚Üź0
              parms.bookmarkLink‚Üź6
              ns‚ÜźP.MarkAPL.Init parms markdown
              ns‚ÜźP.MarkAPL.Process ns
              r‚Üź'<div class="header">',(‚äÉ,/(‚éēUCS 13),¬®ns.html),'</div>'
          :Else
              r‚Üź'<div class="header"></div>'
          :EndIf
      :EndIf
    ‚ąá

    ‚ąá r‚ÜźReplaceDoubleBackslashByNewLine markdown;preMask;fenceMask;bool
      preMask‚Üź~{‚ćĶ‚ą®‚Č†\‚ćĶ}{0<‚ÜĎ‚ćī'^<pre\b[^>]*>' '^</pre>'‚éēS 0‚ć†('Greedy' 0)‚ä£‚ćĶ}¬®markdown
      fenceMask‚ÜźpreMask\~{‚ćĶ‚ą®‚Č†\‚ćĶ}{0<‚ÜĎ‚ćī'\s?~~~' '\s?```'‚éēS 0‚ć†('Greedy' 0)‚äĘ‚ćĶ}¬®preMask/markdown
