     ‚ćĚ Find out how many items belong to a particular list.
     
     ‚ćĚ Note that lists may be nested (one level only) which
     ‚ćĚ means that an ordered list can live inside an unordered
     ‚ćĚ one and vice versa.
      :If 0=type
          noOf‚Üź+/‚ąß\‚ą®/(‚äÉ(2‚ÜĎ¬®(+/‚ąß\' '=‚ÜĎdata_)‚Üď¬®data_))‚ąß.=‚ćČ2 2‚ćī'1.  '
      :ElseIf 1=type
          noOf‚Üź+/‚ąß\(‚ÜĎ¬®(+/‚ąß\' '=‚ÜĎdata_)‚Üď¬®data_)‚ąä'* '
      :Else
          . ‚ćĚ Huuh?!
      :EndIf
     
    ‚ąá

    ‚ąá r‚ÜźCompressList vtv;buffer;sep;noOf;bool;lc;noOf
      ‚ćĚ Takes a vector of character vectors which is supposed to be a list (ordered or not) and
      ‚ćĚ puts lines together that are not separated by a blank line.
      lc‚Üź‚Ćä/+/‚ąß\' '=‚äÉvtv         ‚ćĚ Leading chars
      :If '*'‚ąß.=‚ÜĎ¬®lc
          r‚Üźvtv
      :Else
          r‚Üź''
          :Repeat
              :If 1<noOf‚Üź+/‚ąß\(‚ÜĎ¬®lc‚Üď¬®vtv)=' '
                  buffer‚ÜźnoOf‚ÜĎvtv
                  :If 1=noOf
                      (r[‚ČĘr])‚Üź‚äā((‚ČĘr)‚äÉr),P.APLTreeUtils2.DLB‚ÜĎbuffer
                  :Else
                      (r[‚ČĘr])‚Üź‚äā((‚ČĘr)‚äÉr),‚ÜĎ,/P.APLTreeUtils2.DLB¬®buffer
                  :EndIf
                  vtv‚ÜźnoOf‚Üďvtv
              :Else
                  r,‚Üź‚äā1‚äÉvtv
                  vtv‚Üź1‚Üďvtv
              :EndIf
          :Until 0=‚ČĘvtv
      :EndIf
    ‚ąá

    ‚ąá r‚ÜźGetBase(headerLine scriptRef);buffer;where;parent;bool
      ‚ćĚ Return full path to the base class (if any)
      r‚Üź''
      :If _Inherit
          bool‚Üź~MaskText¬®headerLine
      :AndIf 0‚Č†‚ČĘwhere‚Üź‚ćł‚ą®/¬®':Class '‚ąė‚ć∑¬®bool\¬®bool/¬®headerLine
          buffer‚Üź(1‚äÉwhere)‚äÉheaderLine
